		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Made several improvements to the library tileset and working on enemies. Hopefully the varied bookshelf heights and lighting will be enough to create interesting levels. Instead of sliding down a flag my plan is to collide with a hovering book sprite to signify the end of a level/chapter. I'm obviously borrowing from SMB 3.<br /><div class="attachtitle">Attachment:</div><div class="attachcontent">
			<img src="./download/file.php?id=5108" alt="library.png" /><br />
			<span class="gensmall">library.png [ 11.05 KiB | Viewed 754 times ]</span>
		

		<br />
	</div><br />The bookworm will be a &quot;goomba&quot; and the bookmark will work like a piranha plant. The spider and ghost may get ditched since they will need custom movement routines. I am also thinking of adding a librarian that throws books, like the hammer bros.

		

